01:22.371 --> 01:25.332
<i>We've got an energy crisis, Frank.
And what the White House needs...</i>

01:25.332 --> 01:27.751
The president chose
to remain tough on China.

01:27.918 --> 01:30.420
- <i> No, you forced him to.</i>
- You chose Feng.

01:30.503 --> 01:32.797
<i>You're the one who</i>
<i>put me in a room with him.</i>

01:32.922 --> 01:34.674
<i>The cook can't blame</i>
<i>his ingredients</i>

01:34.841 --> 01:36.342
<i>if he doesn't like</i>
<i>how they taste together.</i>

01:36.467 --> 01:38.636
If samarium prices don't reduce,

01:38.761 --> 01:41.847
the market will have no choice
but to compensate.

01:41.972 --> 01:46.143
That's bad for everyone
who owns an air conditioner.

01:46.268 --> 01:48.019
You should speak to the
president himself.

01:48.144 --> 01:53.566
Well, the president hasn't placed
much value on my advice lately.

01:53.691 --> 01:55.318
I'm in the same boat
as you, Raymond.

01:55.443 --> 01:57.862
<i>Yeah, difference being</i>
<i>you've got an office</i>

01:57.987 --> 02:00.197
three doors down from the Oval.

02:00.322 --> 02:03.534
Let's work together,
for Christ sakes.

02:03.659 --> 02:06.286
I'm willing to put Spotsylvania
behind us if you are.

02:06.411 --> 02:09.580
- <i> I want nothing more.</i>
- Then you'll talk to him?

02:09.705 --> 02:12.250
- Look, I'm late for a meeting, Raymond.
- <i> Yes or no, Frank?</i>

02:12.250 --> 02:15.336
- I can't guarantee he'll listen.
- That's not a yes.

02:15.461 --> 02:17.380
<i>But it's better than a no.</i>

02:17.505 --> 02:19.715
Any pugilist worth his salt
knows when someone's on the ropes,

02:19.840 --> 02:25.095
that's when you throw a combination
to the gut and a left hook to the jaw.

